IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO ESTABLISH AND OPERATE HOUSING PROGRAMS FOR HOMELESS FAMLIES WITH CHILDREN THAT HELP THEM OBTAIN PERMANENT HOUSING AND TO PROVIDE SERVICES TO HELP FAMILIES ACHIEVE ECONOMIC SELF-SUFFICIENCY.
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO ESTABLISH AND OPERATE HOUSING PROGRAMS FOR HOMELESS FAMILIES WITH CHILDREN THAT HELP THEM OBTAIN PERMANENT HOUSING AND TO PROVIDE SERVICES TO HELP FAMILIES ACHIEVE ECONOMIC SELF-SUFFICIENCY.
IRS990.Desc: PROVIDED EMERGENCY SHELTER AND SUPPORTIVE SERVICES FOR 62 HOMELESS FAMILIES INCLUDING 162 CHILDREN. 62% OF FAMILIES SERVED BY NEW DIRECTIONS SHELTER MOVED INTO MORE PERMANENT HOUSING; 100% OF THE ADULTS THAT LOOKED FOR EMPLOYMENT GAINED EMPLOYMENT; 75% OF THE FAMILIES OBTAINED CHILDCARE.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: PROVIDED SUPPORTIVE HOUSING AND SUPPORTIVE SERVICES FOR 36 FAMILIES INCLUDING 93 CHILD. FAMILIES THAT COMPLETED THE PROGRAM INCREASED THEIR MONTHLY HOUSEHOLD INCOME BY 59%. 57% OF THE PARTICIPANTS EXITED TO PERMANENT HOUSING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION'S ENDOWMENT IS TO BE HELD IN PERPETUITY. DISTRIBUTIONS OF UP TO 5% OF THE PRIOR DECEMBER 31 BALANCE CAN BE USED FOR SUPPORT OF THE ORGANIZATION'S PROGRAMS.

THE ORGANIZATION IS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAX UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE. HOWEVER, INCOME, IF ANY, FROM CERTAIN ACTIVITIES NOT DIRECTLY RELATED TO THE ORGANIZATION'S TAX-EXEMPT PURPOSE IS SUBJECT TO TAXATION AS UNRELATED BUSINESS INCOME. IN ADDITION, THE ORGANIZATION QUALIFIES FOR THE CHARITABLE CONTRIBUTION DEDUCTION UNDER SECTION 170(B)(1)(A) AND HAS BEEN CLASSIFIED AS AN ORGANIZATION OTHER THAN A PRIVATE FOUNDATION UNDER SECTION 509(A)(2). THE ORGANIZATION BELIEVES THAT IT HAS APPROPRIATE SUPPORT FOR ANY TAX POSITIONS TAKEN, AND AS SUCH, DOES NOT HAVE ANY UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS THAT ARE MATERIAL TO THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. MANAGEMENT BELIEVES THAT THE ORGANIZATION IS NO LONGER SUBJECT TO INCOME TAX EXAMINATIONS FOR YEARS PRIOR TO 2020.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 4
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ON MAY 18, 2023, THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS APPROVED A MERGER OF BRC-HH, BIDWELL RIVERSIDE CENTER AND HAWTHORN HILL TO BE EFFECTIVE AS OF JULY 1, 2023. HAWTHORN HILL WILL BE THE SURVIVING ENTITY AND THE ORGANIZATION WILL BE RENAMED AS FAMILIES FORWARD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION HAS ONE MEMBER, BRC-HH, THAT PROVIDES MANAGEMENT SERVICES TO THIS AND ONE OTHER NON-PROFIT ORGANZATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE MEMBER HAS THE ABILITY TO SELECT THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD FINANCE COMMITTEE REVIEWS THE FORM 990 PREPARED BY THE OUTSIDE ACCOUNTANT WITH THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR. THE FINANCE COMMITTEE APPROVES THE SUBMISSION OF FORM 990 TO THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY IS APPORVED ANNUALLY BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. ALL BOARD MEMBERS ARE REQUIRED TO SIGN A COPY OF THE POLICY AND DISCLOSE INTERESTS THAT GIVE RISE TO CONFLICTS OF INTEREST. THE BOARD ADDRESSES ANY CONFLICTS OF INTEREST AS NEEDED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: IN DETERMINING THE COMPENSATION OF THE ORGANIZATION'S EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR, A COMPARISON IS DONE FOR SALARIES OF COMPARABLE POSITIONS. SALARIES ARE REVIEWED AND APPROVED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS AND DECISIONS ARE DOCUMENTED IN THE MINUTES OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ALL GOVERNING DOCUMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
